OGE%20recession%3F%20Probably%20not%2C%20but%20the%20ingredients%20are%20there%3A%20mass%20layoffs%20of%20federal%20government%20workers%2C%20large%20cuts%20in%20government%20contracts%20and%20grants%2C%20a%20rapid%20pace%2C%20and%20heightened%20uncertainty%20about%20who%20will%20be%20affected.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fsection%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%223f08ccf4-c296-4fe4-a5b1-baef401e11f4%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EEconomist%C2%A0Cristian%20deRitis%20on%20Moody's%20%26quot%3BInside%20Economics%26quot%3B%20podcast%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.moodys.com%2Fweb%2Fen%2Fus%2Fabout%2Finsights%2Fpodcasts%2Fmoodys-talks-inside-economics%2Fsharing-the-angst.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3ESharing%20the%20Angst%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cblockquote%3E%3Csection%3E%3Cem%3EIt's%20not%20as%20though%20I%20can%2C%20as%20an%20automaker%20or%20manufacturer%2C%20make%20long-term%20plans%20based%20on%20policy%20that's%20changing%20so%20rapidly.%20So%20the%20natural%20response%20to%20that%20type%20of%20uncertainty%20is%20to%20pause%2C%20is%20to%20pull%20back%2C%20and%20that%20could%20certainly%20lead%20to%20slower%20growth%20and%20even%20eventually%20recession%20if%20it%20starts%20to%20spiral%20out%20of%20control%2C%20right%3F%20If%20consumers%20start%20to%20really%20pull%20back%20on%20spending%2C%20businesses%20pull%20back%20on%20their%20hiring%2C%20on%20their%20employment%2C%20that%20leads%20to%20lower%20income%2C%20and%20so%20on%20and%20so%20forth.%20So%20I%20think%20there's%20a%20real%20risk%20here%20that%20the%20uncertainty%20injected%20by%20the%20tariffs%2C%20even%20beyond%20the%20tariffs%20themselves%2C%20could%20do%20some%20real%20economic%20damage.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fsection%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%227495499f-3bc8-48a7-bfb4-c059e25ba9c5%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EEconomics%20professor%20Justin%20Wolfers%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2025%2F03%2F12%2Fopinion%2Ftrump-recession.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3ETwo%20Reasons%20for%20Optimism%20About%20the%20Economy%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cblockquote%3E%3Csection%3E%3Cem%3EWhile%20I'm%20convinced%20that%20our%20current%20recession%20talk%20is%20premature%2C%20I'm%20no%20blind%20optimist.%20America's%20biggest%20economic%20threat%20is%20the%20chaos%20sown%20by%20an%20unpredictable%20White%20House.%20Tariffs%20are%20on%20except%20when%20they're%20off%3B%20DOGE%20cuts%20with%20a%20chain%20saw%20and%20keeps%20hitting%20arteries%3B%20fiscal%20discipline%20has%20gone%20missing%3B%20and%20rule%20by%20executive%20order%20has%20left%20nearly%20the%20entire%20Trump%20agenda%20tied%20up%20in%20court.%20At%20the%20same%20time%2C%20Mr.%20Trump's%20whims%20are%20rewiring%20the%20postwar%20world%20order.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fsection%3E%3Csection%3E%3Cem%3EIf%20there's%20not%20something%20to%20scare%20you%20on%20that%20list%2C%20you're%20not%20paying%20attention.%20Perhaps%20this%20is%20the%20point%20in%20the%20horror%20movie%20when%20you%20wake%20up%20and%20realize%20that%20the%20real%20threat%20is%20coming%20from%20inside%20the%20house.%20Indeed%2C%20that%20fear%20may%20be%20what%20catalyzes%20the%20next%20recession.%20It%20just%20hasn't%20started%20yet.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fsection%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22b7611fe4-d0b2-4225-b729-f99f45c19e34%5C%22%3EFormer%20chief%20economist%20%3Cstrong%3EJared%20Bernstein's%20newsletter%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Feconjared.substack.com%2Fp%2Ftrump-declined-to-rule-out-a-recession%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3ETrump%20Declined%20to%20Rule%20out%20a%20Recession!%20He's%20Right%20(Lutnick's%20Wrong).%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cblockquote%3E%3Csection%3E%3Cem%3ENormal%20people%20just%20want%20to%20know%20how%20all%20this%20chaotic%20economic%20policy%20is%20affecting%20their%20lives%2C%20the%20prices%20they%20face%2C%20interest%20rates%2C%20jobs%2C%20and%20their%20living%20standards%E2%80%A6if%20you%20want%20to%20worry%20more%20about%20recession%2C%20I'm%20with%20you%2C%20though%20the%20odds%20are%20still%20relatively%20low.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fsection%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22d26f6663-290e-41c1-88c3-09ab9cbdfd33%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3ERedfin%20chief%20economist%20Daryl%20Fairweather%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fbsky.app%2Fprofile%2Fhatethegamebook.com%2Fpost%2F3lk4fs6k42c2p%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3ERecession%20risk%20is%20rising%2C%20but%20how%20do%20I%20know%20if%20we're%20in%20a%20recession%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFairweather%20wrote%20on%20Bluesky%20that%20in%20simple%20data%2C%20leading%20indicators%20of%20a%20recession%20include%20an%20inverted%20yield%20curve%2C%20stock%20market%20crash%2C%20weakening%20consumer%20and%20business%20sentiment%2C%20and%20rising%20unemployment%20claims%2C%20as%20well%20as%20more%20dire%20signs%20that%20come%20later%20like%20declining%20personal%20income%20and%20weakening%20GDP.%20She%20added%20that%20%26quot%3Bsome%20warning%20signs%20are%20flashing%2C%20but%20major%20recession%20indicators%20aren't%20confirming%20it%20yet.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%224a5af277-17e4-4dad-84ba-62ec27fc5b17%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EProfessor%20of%20Public%20Policy%20and%20former%20Secretary%20of%20Labor%20Robert%20Reich's%20newsletter%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Frobertreich.substack.com%2Fp%2Fthe-trump-slump-is-now%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20Trump%20Slump%20is%20now%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cblockquote%3E%3Csection%3E%3Cem%3EOver%20the%20weekend%2C%20Trump%20refused%20to%20rule%20out%20a%20recession%20this%20year%2C%20telling%20Fox%20News%20there%20will%20be%20a%20%26quot%3Bperiod%20of%20transition%2C%20because%20what%20we're%20doing%20is%20very%20big.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fsection%3E%3Csection%3E%3Cem%3EWell%2C%20yes%2C%20if%20%26quot%3Bvery%20big%26quot%3B%20means%20destroying%20much%20of%20the%20federal%20government%2C%20allying%20with%20Putin%20against%20our%20traditional%20allies%2C%20and%20putting%20high%20tariff%20walls%20around%20America.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fsection%3E%3Csection%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20cost%20of%20living%20%E2%80%94%20the%20single%20biggest%20problem%20identified%20by%20consumers%20over%20the%20last%20several%20years%20%E2%80%94%20is%20going%20up%2C%20not%20down.%20Trump's%20tariffs%20on%20steel%20and%20aluminum%2C%20and%20his%20threatened%2025%20percent%20tariffs%20on%20Canada%20and%20Mexico%2C%20are%20playing%20havoc%20with%20supply%20chains%20inside%20and%20outside%20America.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fsection%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2234294d94-1a33-4fc0-9424-3ff56c21df12%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3ESenior%20economist%20Dean%20Baker's%20column%20at%20the%20Center%20for%20Economic%20and%20Policy%20Research%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcepr.net%2Fpublications%2Ftrump-musk-recession%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20Trump-Musk%20Recession%3A%20Because%20They%20Can%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cblockquote%3E%3Csection%3E%3Cem%3EAnd%20of%20course%2C%20we%20had%20the%202020%20recession%20because%20of%20the%20COVID-19%20pandemic.%20But%20now%20Donald%20Trump%20is%20threatening%20us%20with%20a%20recession%20%E2%80%94%20not%20because%20of%20something%20that%20is%20any%20way%20unavoidable%2C%20but%20rather%20because%20as%20president%20he%20has%20the%20power%20to%20bring%20on%20a%20recession.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fsection%3E%3Csection%3E%3Cem%3EWhile%20a%20recession%20may%20not%20be%20fully%20baked%20into%20the%20cards%20at%20this%20point%2C%20the%20risk%20is%20evident%20and%20it's%20almost%20entirely%20coming%20from%20Donald%20Trump's%20policies.%20First%20and%20foremost%20are%20the%20costs%20associated%20with%20his%20import%20taxes%20(tariffs)%2C%20or%2